I21The District of Columbia was added as a separate circuit. This is in accord with the decision of the Supreme Court of the United States which held the Court of Appeals for the District of Columbia to be a circuit court of appeals within the Transfer Act of Sept. 14, 1922, ch. 305, 42 Stat. 837, incorporated in the Judicial Code as ÿ1A238(a), but repealed by act Feb. 13, 1925, ch. 229, ÿ1A13, 43 Stat. 942. (See T3Swift and Co. v. U.SK., 1928, 48 S.Ct. 311, 276 U.S. 311, 72 L.Ed. 587.)

