I89. Courts always open; powers unrestricted by expiration of sessions

I11All courts of the United States shall be deemed always open for the purpose of filing proper papers, issuing and returning process, and making motions and orders.

I11The continued existence or expiration of a session of a court in no way affects the power of the court to do any act or take any proceeding.

