I21The phrase ``always open'' means ``never closed'' and signifies the time when a court can exercise its functions. With respect to matters enumerated by statute or rule as to which the court is ``always open,'' there is no time when the court is without power to act. (Ex parte Branch, 63 Ala. 383, 387.)

