I89. United States trustees

I11(a) The Attorney General shall appoint one United States trustee for each of the following regions composed of Federal judicial districts (without regard to section 451):

I12(1) The judicial districts established for the States of Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, and Rhode Island.

I12(2) The judicial districts established for the States of Connecticut, New York, and Vermont.

I12(3) The judicial districts established for the States of Delaware, New Jersey, and Pennsylvania.

I12(4) The judicial districts established for the States of Maryland, North Carolina, South Carolina, Virginia, and West Virginia and for the District of Columbia.

I12(5) The judicial districts established for the States of Louisiana and Mississippi.

I12(6) The Northern District of Texas and the Eastern District of Texas.

I12(7) The Southern District of Texas and the Western District of Texas.

I12(8) The judicial districts established for the States of Kentucky and Tennessee.

I12(9) The judicial districts established for the States of Michigan and Ohio.

I12(10) The Central District of Illinois and the Southern District of Illinois; and the judicial districts established for the State of Indiana.

I12(11) The Northern District of Illinois; and the judicial districts established for the State of Wisconsin.

I12(12) The judicial districts established for the States of Minnesota, Iowa, North Dakota, and South Dakota.

I12(13) The judicial districts established for the States of Arkansas, Nebraska, and Missouri.

I12(14) The District of Arizona.

I12(15) The Southern District of California; and the judicial districts established for the State of Hawaii, and for Guam and the Commonwealth of the Northern Mariana Islands.

I12(16) The Central District of California.

I12(17) The Eastern District of California and the Northern District of California; and the judicial district established for the State of Nevada.

I12(18) The judicial districts established for the States of Alaska, Idaho (exclusive of Yellowstone National Park), Montana (exclusive of Yellowstone National Park), Oregon, and Washington.

I12(19) The judicial districts established for the States of Colorado, Utah, and Wyoming (including those portions of Yellowstone National Park situated in the States of Montana and Idaho).

I12(20) The judicial districts established for the States of Kansas, New Mexico, and Oklahoma.

I12(21) The judicial districts established for the States of Alabama, Florida, and Georgia and for the Commonwealth of Puerto Rico and the Virgin Islands of the United States.

Q04

I11(b) Each United States trustee shall be appointed for a term of five years. On the expiration of his term, a United States trustee shall continue to perform the duties of his office until his successor is appointed and qualifies.

I11(c) Each United States trustee is subject to removal by the Attorney General.

