I89. Original jurisdiction

I11(a) The Supreme Court shall have original and exclusive jurisdiction of all controversies between two or more States.

I11(b) The Supreme Court shall have original but not exclusive jurisdiction of:

I12(1) All actions or proceedings to which ambassadors, other public ministers, consuls, or vice consuls of foreign states are parties;

I12(2) All controversies between the United States and a State;

I12(3) All actions or proceedings by a State against the citizens of another State or against aliens.

