I80ÿ1A1605

I89. General exceptions to the jurisdictional immunity of a foreign state

I11(a) A foreign state shall not be immune from the jurisdiction of courts of the United States or of the States in any case_

I12(1) in which the foreign state has waived its immunity either explicitly or by implication, notwithstanding any withdrawal of the waiver which the foreign state may purport to effect except in accordance with the terms of the waiver;

