I11(f) A court of a State may modify a determination of the custody of the same child made by a court of another State, if_

I12(1) it has jurisdiction to make such a child custody determination; and

I12(2) the court of the other State no longer has jurisdiction, or it has declined to exercise such jurisdiction to modify such determination.

