I81Rule 2. The Motion

I11(a) T4Applying for ReliefK. The application must be in the form of a motion to vacate, set aside, or correct the sentence.

I11(b) T4FormK. The motion must:

I12(1) specify all the grounds for relief available to the moving party;

I12(2) state the facts supporting each ground;

I12(3) state the relief requested;

I12(4) be printed, typewritten, or legibly handwritten; and

I12(5) be signed under penalty of perjury by the movant or by a person authorized to sign it for the movant.

Q04

I11(c) T4Standard FormK. The motion must substantially follow either the form appended to these rules or a form prescribed by a local district-court rule. The clerk must make forms available to moving parties without charge.

I11(d) T4Separate Motions for Separate JudgmentsK. A moving party who seeks relief from more than one judgment must file a separate motion covering each judgment.

