I80ÿ1A2715

I89. Publication

I11The marshal shall cause publication of an executed warrant of attachment_

I12(1) for two months in case of an absconding debtor, and

I12(2) for four months in case of a nonresident debtor

Q04

I10in a newspaper published in the district where the property is situated pursuant to the details of the order under which the warrant is issued.

I53(Added Pub. L. 86ÿ09682, ÿ1A9, Sept. 2, 1960, 74 Stat. 707.)

I76Codification

I21Section was derived from R.S. ÿ1A929, which was originally classified to section 742 of former Title 28. Following the general revision and enactment of Title 28 by act June 25, 1948, R.S. ÿ1A929 was reclassified to section 842 of Title 39. R.S. ÿ1A929 was repealed by Pub. L. 86ÿ09682, ÿ1A12(c), Sept. 2, 1960, 74 Stat. 708, (section 1 of which revised and enacted Title 39), and reenacted by section 9 thereof as section 2715 of this title.

I80ÿ1A2716

I89. Personal notice

I11After the first publication of the notice of attachment, a person indebted to, or having possession of property of a defendant and having knowledge of the notice, shall answer for the amount of his debt or the value of the property. Any disposal or attempted disposal of the property, to the injury of the United States, is unlawful. When the person indebted to, or having possession of the property of a defendant, is known to the United States attorney or marshal, the officer shall cause a personal notice of the attachment to be served upon him, but the lack of the notice does not invalidate the attachment.

I53(Added Pub. L. 86ÿ09682, ÿ1A9, Sept. 2, 1960, 74 Stat. 707.)

I76Codification

I21Section was derived from R.S. ÿ1A930, which was originally classified to section 743 of former Title 28. Following the general revision and enactment of Title 28 by act June 25, 1948, R.S. ÿ1A930 was reclassified to section 843 of Title 39. R.S. ÿ1A930 was repealed by Pub. L. 86ÿ09682, ÿ1A12(c), Sept. 2, 1960, 74 Stat. 708, (section 1 of which revised and enacted Title 39), and reenacted by section 9 thereof as section 2716 of this title.

I80ÿ1A2717

I89. Discharge

I11The court, or a judge thereof, upon_

I12(1) application of the party when property has been attached and

I12(2) execution to the United States of a penal bond, approved by a judge, in double the value of the property attached and conditioned upon the return of the property or the payment of any judgment rendered by the court

Q04

I10may discharge the warrant of attachment as to the property of the applicant.

I53(Added Pub. L. 86ÿ09682, ÿ1A9, Sept. 2, 1960, 74 Stat. 708.)

I76Codification

I21Section was derived from R.S. ÿ1A931, which was originally classified to section 744 of former Title 28. Following the general revision and enactment of Title 28 by act June 25, 1948, R.S. ÿ1A931 was reclassified to section 844 of Title 39. R.S. ÿ1A931 was repealed by Pub. L. 86ÿ09682, ÿ1A12(c), Sept. 2, 1960, 74 Stat. 708, (section 1 of which revised and enacted Title 39), and reenacted by section 9 thereof as section 2717 of this title.

I80ÿ1A2718

I89. Interest on balances due department

I11In suits for balances due the Post Office Department may recover interest at the rate of 6 per centum per year from the time of default.

I53(Added Pub. L. 86ÿ09682, ÿ1A9, Sept. 2, 1960, 74 Stat. 708.)

