I89. Insolvency

I11(a) T4In GeneralK._Except as provided in subsection (c), a debtor is insolvent if the sum of the debtor's debts is greater than all of the debtor's assets at a fair valuation.

I11(b) T4PresumptionK._A debtor who is generally not paying debts as they become due is presumed to be insolvent.

I11(c) T4CalculationK._A partnership is insolvent under subsection (a) if the sum of the partnership's debts is greater than the aggregate, at a fair valuation, of_

I12(1) all of the partnership's assets; and

I12(2) the sum of the excess of the value of each general partner's non-partnership assets over the partner's non-partnership debts.

