I89. Definitions

I11In this chapter:

I12(1) T4DefamationK._The term ``defamation'' means any action or other proceeding for defamation, libel, slander, or similar claim alleging that forms of speech are false, have caused damage to reputation or emotional distress, have presented any person in a false light, or have resulted in criticism, dishonor, or condemnation of any person.

I12(2) T4Domestic courtK._The term ``domestic court'' means a Federal court or a court of any State.

I12(3) T4Foreign courtK._The term ``foreign court'' means a court, administrative body, or other tribunal of a foreign country.

I12(4) T4Foreign judgmentK._The term ``foreign judgment'' means a final judgment rendered by a foreign court.

I12(5) T4StateK._The term ``State'' means each of the several States, the District of Columbia, and any commonwealth, territory, or possession of the United States.

I12(6) T4United states personK._The term ``United States person'' means_

I13(A) a United States citizen;

I13(B) an alien lawfully admitted for permanent residence to the United States;

I13(C) an alien lawfully residing in the United States at the time that the speech that is the subject of the foreign defamation action was researched, prepared, or disseminated; or

I13(D) a business entity incorporated in, or with its primary location or place of operation in, the United States.

